Class CaselessProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Dictionary<K,V>
      • java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.Object,java.lang.Object>
        • java.util.Properties
          • org.concordion.cubano.config.CaselessProperties
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.Object,java.lang.Object>

    public class CaselessProperties
extends java.util.Properties

    A Properties implementation that ignores the case of the properties.

    The keys are stored untouched so that if you need the original case you can still get them using Enumeration<String> en = (Enumeration) properties.propertyNames();
